If you want to install the Gene clustering command-line package, here are the requirements:

1/ The latest version of the package is available from http://genome.imim.es/webservices/downloads/GeneClustering_Workflow_Script.tar.gz

2/ It has only been tested on a Unix-like system (Linux or MacOSX)

3/ The Perl programming language v5.8 or later

	=> http://www.perl.org

4/ The BioMOBY Perl API, v0.8.2a

	=> http://biomoby.org/PerlReleases/biomoby.0.8.2a.tar.gz

5/ The following Perl module dependencies that can be downloaded from CPAN (http://www.cpan.org)

	* SOAP::Lite v0.60 (it won't work with more recent versions of SOAP::Lite !!)
	* MIME-Base64
	* XML::Sax
	* XML::LibXML::Common
	* XML::NamespaceSupport
	* XML::LibXML
	* HTML::Entities

6/ Make sure all these libraries are in PERL5LIB environment variable

7/ You also need the meta-alignment software to perform the pairwise alignments locally, when you are working on a huge dataset

	The sources can be downloaded from here: ftp://genome.imim.es/pub/software/meta/meta_v1.1.Oct_28_2005.tar.gz
	More information about installing it, http://genome.imim.es/software/meta/index.html#code

	Then Setup META environment variable to point to the meta binary:
	SH: export META=path_to_meta/bin/meta
	CSH: setenv META path_to_meta/bin/meta
